{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":1160,"text":"I'm the product\nof a bold leadership decision."},{"time":4920,"text":"After 1956, when Tunisia\nbecame independent,"},{"time":8920,"text":"our first president, Habib Bourguiba,"},{"time":11680,"text":"decided to invest 20 percent\nof the country's national budget"},{"time":15560,"text":"in education."},{"time":17160,"text":"Yes, 20 percent,"},{"time":18760,"text":"on the high end of the spectrum\neven by today's standards."},{"time":22480,"text":"Some people protested."},{"time":24400,"text":"What about infrastructure?"},{"time":26120,"text":"What about electricity,\nroads and running water?"},{"time":29160,"text":"Are these not important?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":32159,"text":"I would argue"},{"time":33640,"text":"that the most important\ninfrastructure we have are minds,"},{"time":38360,"text":"educated minds."},{"time":41280,"text":"President Bourguiba helped establish\nfree, high-quality education"},{"time":47520,"text":"for every boy and every girl."},{"time":51760,"text":"And together with millions\nof other Tunisians,"},{"time":54840,"text":"I'm deeply indebted\nto that historic decision."}]},{"cues":[{"time":58040,"text":"And that's what brought me here today,"},{"time":61280,"text":"because today, we are facing\na global learning crisis."},{"time":65840,"text":"I call it learning crisis\nand not education crisis,"},{"time":69200,"text":"because on top of\nthe quarter of a billion children"},{"time":72160,"text":"who are out of school today,"},{"time":74800,"text":"even more, 330 million children,"},{"time":78880,"text":"are in school but failing to learn."},{"time":83760,"text":"And if we do nothing,"},{"time":85600,"text":"if nothing changes,"},{"time":87280,"text":"by 2030, just 13 years from now,"},{"time":91280,"text":"half of the world's children and youth,"},{"time":94840,"text":"half of 1.6 billion children and youth,"},{"time":98920,"text":"will be either out of school\nor failing to learn."}]},{"cues":[{"time":106240,"text":"So two years ago,\nI joined the Education Commission."},{"time":110080,"text":"It's a commission brought together\nby former UK Prime Minister"},{"time":113840,"text":"and UN Special Envoy\nfor Global Education Gordon Brown."},{"time":117960,"text":"Our first task was to find out:"},{"time":120040,"text":"How big is the learning crisis?"},{"time":121720,"text":"What's actually the scope of the problem?"},{"time":124840,"text":"Today we know:"},{"time":126320,"text":"half of the world's children by 2030"},{"time":129520,"text":"will be failing to learn."},{"time":132000,"text":"And that's how actually we discovered"},{"time":133960,"text":"that we need to change the world's focus\nfrom schooling to learning,"},{"time":138680,"text":"from just counting\nhow many bodies are in classrooms"},{"time":141440,"text":"to actually how many are learning."},{"time":144320,"text":"And the second big task was,"},{"time":147520,"text":"can we do anything about this?"},{"time":149760,"text":"Can we do anything\nabout this big, vast, silent,"},{"time":153200,"text":"maybe most-neglected international crisis?"},{"time":156640,"text":"And what we found out is, we can."},{"time":159840,"text":"It's actually amazing."},{"time":162000,"text":"We can, for the first time,"},{"time":164200,"text":"have every child in school and learning"},{"time":167840,"text":"within just one generation."},{"time":171840,"text":"And we don't even have to really\ninvent the wheel to do so."},{"time":175600,"text":"We just need to learn\nfrom the best in class,"},{"time":178760,"text":"but not any best in class --"},{"time":181080,"text":"the best in your own class."}]},{"cues":[{"time":184200,"text":"What we did is actually\nwe looked at countries by income level:"},{"time":187960,"text":"low-income, mid-income, high-income."},{"time":190720,"text":"We looked at what the 25 percent\nfastest improvers in education do,"},{"time":195760,"text":"and what we found out is"},{"time":197680,"text":"that if every country moves\nat the same rate as the fastest improvers"},{"time":202200,"text":"within their own income level,"},{"time":204680,"text":"then within just one generation"},{"time":207080,"text":"we can have every child\nin school and learning."}]},{"cues":[{"time":211880,"text":"Let me give you an example."},{"time":214000,"text":"Let's take Tunisia for example."},{"time":215960,"text":"We're not telling Tunisia,\n\"You should move as fast as Finland.\""},{"time":219760,"text":"No disrespect, Finland."},{"time":221720,"text":"We're telling Tunisia,"},{"time":223120,"text":"\"Look at Vietnam.\""},{"time":224480,"text":"They spend similar amounts\nfor primary and secondary pupils"},{"time":228840,"text":"as percentage of GDP per capita,"},{"time":231160,"text":"but achieves today higher results."},{"time":234440,"text":"Vietnam introduced a standardized\nassessment for literacy and numeracy,"},{"time":239120,"text":"teachers in Vietnam are better monitored\nthan in other developing countries,"},{"time":243880,"text":"and students' achievements\nare made public."},{"time":248000,"text":"And it shows in the results."},{"time":250160,"text":"In the 2015 PISA --"},{"time":252120,"text":"Program for International\nStudent Assessment --"},{"time":254800,"text":"Vietnam outperformed\nmany wealthy economies,"},{"time":257640,"text":"including the United States."}]},{"cues":[{"time":261680,"text":"Now, if you're not an education expert,"},{"time":264720,"text":"you may ask, \"What's new and different?"},{"time":266680,"text":"Don't all countries track student progress\nand make those achievements public?\""},{"time":272040,"text":"No. The sad answer is no."},{"time":275000,"text":"We are very far from it."},{"time":277400,"text":"Only half of the developing countries"},{"time":279920,"text":"have systematic learning assessment\nat primary school,"},{"time":282960,"text":"and even less so\nat lower secondary school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":287080,"text":"So if we don't know"},{"time":290360,"text":"if children are learning,"},{"time":292080,"text":"how are teachers supposed to focus\ntheir attention on delivering results,"},{"time":296040,"text":"and how are countries supposed\nto prioritize education spending"},{"time":299640,"text":"actually to delivering results,"},{"time":301160,"text":"if they don't know\nif children are learning?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":304600,"text":"That's why the first big transformation"},{"time":308480,"text":"before investing"},{"time":310280,"text":"is to make the education system\ndeliver results."},{"time":315160,"text":"Because pouring more money\ninto broken systems"},{"time":318920,"text":"may only fund more inefficiencies."},{"time":322240,"text":"And what deeply worries me --"},{"time":324080,"text":"if children go to school and don't learn,"},{"time":327320,"text":"it devalues education,"},{"time":329080,"text":"and it devalues spending on education,"},{"time":331280,"text":"so that governments\nand political parties can say,"},{"time":334000,"text":"\"Oh, we are spending\nso much money on education,"},{"time":336280,"text":"but children are not learning."},{"time":337760,"text":"They don't have the right skills."},{"time":339760,"text":"Maybe we should spend less.\""}]},{"cues":[{"time":342080,"text":"Now, improving current\neducation systems to deliver results"},{"time":346720,"text":"is important, but won't be enough."},{"time":350000,"text":"What about countries where\nwe won't have enough qualified teachers?"},{"time":353200,"text":"Take Somalia, for example."},{"time":354480,"text":"If every student in Somalia\nbecame a teacher --"},{"time":357520,"text":"every person who finishes\ntertiary education became a teacher --"},{"time":360640,"text":"we won't have enough teachers."},{"time":364160,"text":"And what about children in refugee camps,"},{"time":367240,"text":"or in very remote rural areas?"}]},{"cues":[{"time":370280,"text":"Take Filipe, for example."},{"time":372480,"text":"Filipe lives in one\nof the thousands of communities"},{"time":375720,"text":"alongside the Amazonas rivers."},{"time":378400,"text":"His village of 78 people has 20 families."},{"time":382680,"text":"Filipe and a fellow student"},{"time":384520,"text":"were the only two\nattending grade 11 in 2015."},{"time":389080,"text":"Now, the Amazonas is a state\nin the northwest of Brazil."},{"time":393120,"text":"It's four and a half times\nthe size of Germany,"},{"time":395760,"text":"and it's fully covered\nin jungle and rivers."},{"time":399120,"text":"A decade ago, Filipe\nand his fellow student"},{"time":401960,"text":"would have had just two alternatives:"},{"time":405000,"text":"moving to Manaus, the capital,\nor stopping studying altogether,"},{"time":409200,"text":"which most of them did."},{"time":412600,"text":"In 2009, however, Brazil passed a new law"},{"time":416040,"text":"that made secondary education\na guarantee for every Brazilian"},{"time":420600,"text":"and an obligation for every state\nto implement this by 2016."},{"time":425600,"text":"But giving access\nto high-quality education,"},{"time":428840,"text":"you know, in the Amazonas state,\nis huge and expensive."},{"time":431560,"text":"How are you going to get, you know,\nmath and science and history teachers"},{"time":435040,"text":"all over those communities?"},{"time":436400,"text":"And even if you find them,"},{"time":438040,"text":"many of them would not want to move there."},{"time":441440,"text":"So faced with this impossible task,"},{"time":444000,"text":"civil servants and state officials"},{"time":446360,"text":"developed amazing creativity\nand entrepreneurship."},{"time":450120,"text":"They developed the media center solution."},{"time":452120,"text":"It works this way."},{"time":453400,"text":"You have specialized,\ntrained content teachers in Manaus"},{"time":458840,"text":"delivering classroom via livestream"},{"time":461240,"text":"to over a thousand classrooms\nin those scattered communities."},{"time":465160,"text":"Those classrooms have five to 25 students,"},{"time":468280,"text":"and they're supported\nby a more generalist tutoring teacher"},{"time":471920,"text":"for their learning and development."},{"time":474480,"text":"The 60 content teachers in Manaus"},{"time":476840,"text":"work with over 2,200 tutoring teachers\nin those communities"},{"time":482320,"text":"to customize lesson plans\nto the context and time."}]},{"cues":[{"time":487440,"text":"Now, why is this division"},{"time":489400,"text":"between content teacher\nand tutoring teacher important?"},{"time":494600,"text":"First of all, as I told you,\nbecause in many countries,"},{"time":497240,"text":"we just don't have\nenough qualified teachers."},{"time":499920,"text":"But secondly also because\nteachers do too many things"},{"time":503240,"text":"they're either not trained for\nor not supposed to do."}]},{"cues":[{"time":507040,"text":"Let's look at Chile, for example."},{"time":509560,"text":"In Chile, for every doctor,"},{"time":511720,"text":"you have four and a half people,"},{"time":513679,"text":"four and a half staff supporting them,"},{"time":516520,"text":"and Chile is on the low end\nof the spectrum here,"},{"time":521880,"text":"because in developing countries,\non average, every doctor"},{"time":524640,"text":"has 10 people supporting them."},{"time":527720,"text":"A teacher in Chile, however,"},{"time":529680,"text":"has less than half a person,"},{"time":532440,"text":"0.3 persons, supporting them."}]},{"cues":[{"time":536360,"text":"Imagine a hospital ward\nwith 20, 40, 70 patients"},{"time":540760,"text":"and you have a doctor\ndoing it all by themselves:"},{"time":543840,"text":"no nurses, no medical assistants,"},{"time":546280,"text":"no one else."},{"time":548360,"text":"You will say this is\nabsurd and impossible,"},{"time":550720,"text":"but this is what teachers are doing\nall over the world every day"},{"time":554240,"text":"with classrooms of 20, 40, or 70 students."}]},{"cues":[{"time":558400,"text":"So this division between content\nand tutoring teachers is amazing"},{"time":562040,"text":"because it is changing\nthe paradigm of the teacher,"},{"time":565000,"text":"so that each does what they can do best"},{"time":567240,"text":"and so that children\nare not just in school"},{"time":569480,"text":"but in school and learning."},{"time":572640,"text":"And some of these content teachers,"},{"time":574600,"text":"they became celebrity teachers."},{"time":576800,"text":"You know, some of them run for office,"},{"time":578680,"text":"and they helped raise\nthe status of the profession"},{"time":581520,"text":"so that more students\nwanted to become teachers."}]},{"cues":[{"time":585960,"text":"And what I love about this example"},{"time":588000,"text":"is beyond changing\nthe paradigm of the teacher."},{"time":591400,"text":"It teaches us how we can harness\ntechnology for learning."},{"time":595400,"text":"The live-streaming is bidirectional,"},{"time":597800,"text":"so students like Filipe and others\ncan present information back."},{"time":602360,"text":"And we know technology\nis not always perfect."},{"time":605240,"text":"You know, state officials expect"},{"time":606840,"text":"between five to 15 percent\nof the classrooms"},{"time":608960,"text":"every day to be off live-stream"},{"time":611080,"text":"because of flood, broken antennas\nor internet not working."},{"time":615160,"text":"And yet, Filipe is one\nof over 300,000 students"},{"time":619960,"text":"that benefited from\nthe media center solution"},{"time":622160,"text":"and got access to postprimary education."},{"time":626120,"text":"This is a living example"},{"time":628000,"text":"how technology is not just an add-on"},{"time":630880,"text":"but can be central to learning\nand can help us bring school to children"},{"time":635520,"text":"if we cannot bring children to school."}]},{"cues":[{"time":641320,"text":"Now, I hear you."},{"time":642800,"text":"You're going to say,"},{"time":644240,"text":"\"How are we going to implement this\nall over the world?\""},{"time":647480,"text":"I've been in government myself"},{"time":649040,"text":"and have seen how difficult it is\neven to implement the best ideas."},{"time":654240,"text":"So as a commission,\nwe started two initiatives"},{"time":657160,"text":"to make the \"Learning\nGeneration\" a reality."},{"time":660400,"text":"The first one is called\nthe Pioneer Country Initiative."},{"time":663560,"text":"Over 20 countries from Africa and Asia"},{"time":666120,"text":"have committed to make\neducation their priority"},{"time":669080,"text":"and to transform their education\nsystems to deliver results."},{"time":672880,"text":"We've trained country leaders"},{"time":674320,"text":"in a methodology\ncalled the delivery approach."},{"time":677120,"text":"What this does is basically two things."},{"time":679040,"text":"In the planning phase,\nwe take everyone into a room --"},{"time":682360,"text":"teachers, teacher unions,\nparent associations,"},{"time":684800,"text":"government officials, NGOs, everyone --"},{"time":687360,"text":"so that the reform\nand the solution we come up with"},{"time":689765,"text":"are shared by everyone\nand supported by everyone."},{"time":693320,"text":"And in the second phase,"},{"time":695280,"text":"it does something special."},{"time":697680,"text":"It's kind of a ruthless\nfocus on follow-up."},{"time":702440,"text":"So week by week you check,"},{"time":705320,"text":"has that been done,\nwhat was supposed to be done,"},{"time":708000,"text":"and even sometimes sending a person\nphysically to the district or school"},{"time":712640,"text":"to check that versus\njust hoping that it happened."},{"time":717960,"text":"It may sound for many common sense,"},{"time":720400,"text":"but it's not common practice,"},{"time":721920,"text":"and that's why actually many reforms fail."},{"time":726040,"text":"It has been piloted in Tanzania,"},{"time":728720,"text":"and there the pass rate\nfor students in secondary education"},{"time":734320,"text":"was increased by 50 percent\nin just over two years."}]},{"cues":[{"time":740960,"text":"Now, the next initiative\nto make the Learning Generation a reality"},{"time":744560,"text":"is financing. Who's going to pay for this?"},{"time":748040,"text":"So we believe and argue"},{"time":749480,"text":"that domestic financing has to be\nthe backbone of education investment."},{"time":753680,"text":"Do you remember when I told you\nabout Vietnam earlier"},{"time":756280,"text":"outperforming the United States in PISA?"},{"time":759240,"text":"That's due to a better education system,"},{"time":761400,"text":"but also to Vietnam\nincreasing their investment"},{"time":764000,"text":"from seven to 20 percent\nof their national budget in two decades."}]},{"cues":[{"time":769160,"text":"But what happens if countries\nwant to borrow money for education?"},{"time":772960,"text":"If you wanted to borrow money\nto build a bridge or a road,"},{"time":776200,"text":"it's quite easy and straightforward,"},{"time":778400,"text":"but not for education."},{"time":780680,"text":"It's easier to make a shiny picture\nof a bridge and show it to everyone"},{"time":784720,"text":"than one of an educated mind."},{"time":787320,"text":"That's kind of a longer term commitment."}]},{"cues":[{"time":790555,"text":"So we came up with a solution"},{"time":791960,"text":"to help countries escape\nthe middle income trap,"},{"time":795160,"text":"countries that are not poor enough\nor not poor, thankfully, anymore,"},{"time":799400,"text":"that cannot profit from grants\nor interest-free loans,"},{"time":802920,"text":"and they're not rich enough"},{"time":804440,"text":"to be able to have attractive\ninterests on their loans."},{"time":807920,"text":"So we're pooling donor money\nin a finance facility for education,"},{"time":811880,"text":"which will provide\nmore finance for education."},{"time":814280,"text":"We will subsidize,\nor even eliminate completely,"},{"time":817560,"text":"interest payments on the loans"},{"time":819520,"text":"so that countries that commit to reforms"},{"time":821840,"text":"can borrow money,"},{"time":823520,"text":"reform their education system,\nand pay this money over time"},{"time":827000,"text":"while benefiting\nfrom a better-educated population."},{"time":831000,"text":"This solution has been recognized\nin the last G20 meeting in Germany,"},{"time":835600,"text":"and so finally today\neducation is on the international agenda."}]},{"cues":[{"time":842160,"text":"But let me bring this back\nto the personal level,"},{"time":845520,"text":"because this is where the impact lands."},{"time":849120,"text":"Without that decision\nto invest a young country's budget,"},{"time":853320,"text":"20 percent of a young country's\nbudget in education,"},{"time":856960,"text":"I would have never\nbeen able to go to school,"},{"time":860120,"text":"let alone in 2014"},{"time":862160,"text":"becoming a minister in the government"},{"time":864080,"text":"that successfully ended\nthe transition phase."},{"time":867480,"text":"Tunisia's Nobel Peace Prize in 2015"},{"time":870200,"text":"as the only democracy\nthat emerged from the Arab Spring"},{"time":873600,"text":"is a legacy to that bold\nleadership decision."},{"time":878440,"text":"Education is the civil rights struggle,"},{"time":881240,"text":"it's the human rights struggle\nof our generation."},{"time":884640,"text":"Quality education for all:"},{"time":886680,"text":"that's the freedom fight\nthat we've got to win."}]},{"cues":[{"time":891160,"text":"Thank you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":892400,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}